&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;&lt;span&gt;Consultant in Obstetrics &amp; Gynaecology&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Bedford Hospital NHS Trust is seeking to appoint a full time Locum Consultant Obstetrician &amp; Gynaecologist for a period of six months. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The post will include rotational cover of the Delivery Suite and the successful candidate will take part in a 1 in 4 Monday to Thursday on call rota and 1 in 8 weekend on-call &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Candidates must be a member of the Royal College of Obstetricians &amp; Gynaecologists, have full GMC registration and licence to practice. Excellent communication and team working skills are essential.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;An informal visit may be arranged by appointment with Mr Montasser Mahran Consultant Obstetrician &amp; Gynaecologist (&lt;/span&gt;01234 730358, secretary&lt;span&gt;).&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
